Package: simphony
Title: Simulating large-scale, rhythmic data
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: as.person(c(
  "Jordan Singer <jordan.m.singer@gmail.com> [aut, cre]",
  "Darwin Fu <darwinyfu@gmail.com> [ctb]",
  "Jake Hughey <jakejhughey@gmail.com> [ctb]"))
Description: A tool for simulating rhythmic data: transcriptome data using
  Gaussian or negative binomial distributions, and behavioral activity data
  using Bernoulli or Poisson distributions.
Depends: R (>= 3.4)
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
URL: https://github.com/hugheylab/simphony
